articles.title: Complimenting your partner could actually be harmful, expert warns â€” two things you should never say
articles.content: Compliments can certainly go a long way in making someone feel special and loved. While you might think everyone loves a little flattery, one expert warns that some compliments may have unintended negative impacts on romantic relationships. â€œCompliments can be disarming. They make us feel chosen and understood in ways that other words rarely do,â€ the psychologist explained. â€œBut sometimes, the praise that feels the most flattering is also the praise that teaches us to edit ourselves.â€. If your partner grew up playing the peacekeeper in chaotic situations, this compliment might feel like overdue recognition. Yet, it can also come across as a reward for their silence.
